Gaps / Blockers
1) Blockers for moving to main domain as project root
- Frontend is already rooted at '/' for landing, but tenant storefront/admin are hardwired to /store/:slug paths.
- Existing platform-generated URLs still use query-style tenant links (/store?tenant=..., /admin?tenant=...) which do not match current router patterns.
- Sources:
  - frontend/src/app/app.routes.ts
  - frontend/src/app/platform/pages/tenants/tenant-create.component.ts
  - frontend/src/app/platform/pages/tenants/tenant-detail.component.ts

2) Blockers for subdomain per store
- No host/subdomain parsing in frontend or backend tenant resolution.
- Backend strictly resolves via X-Tenant-Slug, not Request.Host.
- No tenant subdomain field in data model.
- Sources:
  - src/NovaNode.Api/Middleware/TenantResolutionMiddleware.cs
  - src/NovaNode.Domain/Entities/Tenant.cs

3) Blockers for custom domain per tenant
- No custom-domain persistence fields.
- No domain verification fields/workflow.
- No host-to-tenant mapping logic.
- No domain-level active/verified state.
- Sources:
  - src/NovaNode.Domain/Entities/Tenant.cs
  - src/NovaNode.Infrastructure/Persistence/AppDbContext.cs
  - src/NovaNode.Api/Middleware/TenantResolutionMiddleware.cs

4) Blockers for tenant admin on tenant domain
- Admin URLs are path-based under /store/:slug/admin.
- Auth guard/store isolation currently compares route-derived slug vs session-stored slug.
- Backend still requires X-Tenant-Slug header for tenant-scoped endpoints; host/domain alone cannot resolve tenant.
- Sources:
  - frontend/src/app/app.routes.ts
  - frontend/src/app/core/guards/auth.guard.ts
